0027|- [HelpText]
0028|*The right edge of the text on consecutive lines is adjusted to a selected
0029|*width of W picas (1 inch=12 picas) by the control word - [trim(W)] .
0030|*PRINT never changes division of text into lines. This must be done by
0031|*the user by TRIM operations before printing.
0032|*On variable pitch fonts (Times, Helvetica etc.) the typical form of
0033|- shadow %: [LINK(q06_01.html)] [/LINK]
0034|*TRIM (see TRIM? for other forms) is
S   |           %%%%
0035|*TRIM3 L1,L2,C,<font_type>
S   |               <         >
0036|*where L1-L2 are lines to be adjusted, C is the selected width and 'P'
0037|*means proportional trimming. The last parameter <font_type> is one of
S   |                                                 <         >
0038|*the alternatives
0039|*  P3 Times
0040|*  P4 Swiss (Helvetica)
0041|*  P5 Avant Garde                These fonts are defined in PSFONTS.DV2
0042|*  P6 Bookman
0043|*  P7 New Century Schoolbook
0044|*  P8 Palatino
0045|*  P9 Zapf Chancery
0047|*The proper C value depends simultaneously on the final printing width W
0048|*(in picas) and font size S (in points) by the formula C=12*W/S.
0049|*Of course, if a line consists of text in different font sizes,
0050|*individual editing might be needed. In normal text no extra adjustment
0051|*is necessary. For example, in case - [Times(10)][trim(50)] (i.e. S=10,
0052|*W=50) a good value for TRIM is C=12*50/10=60.
0054|*To change the width, use another - [trim()] and to abandon the right
0055|*edge alignment, use - [trim(0)]. Any line can be temporarily freed from
0056|*adjustment by putting 'U' in the control column.
0058|*The simplest way to adjust lines in proportional pitch is to use the
0059|*sucro /TRIMP.
