0111|- [HelpText]
0112|*On the PostScript printers the - picture control line can have a more
0113|*general form
0114|* - picture <file.PS>,x,y,kx,ky,z
S   |            <       >
0115|*where the extra (optional) parameters are scaling coefficients kx,ky
0116|*and angle of rotation z in degrees. If z is positive, the picture
0117|*will first be scaled and then rotated. If z is negative, the picture
0118|*will first be rotated and then scaled by angle -z.
0119|*Furthermore, x and y can be replaced by relative coordinates of the form *+C
0120|*or *-C where C is a constant. The reference level * of y is the base
0121|*level of the current line and the reference level * of x is the current
0122|*start position of the line (determined by the left margin).
0123|*This feature greatly simplifies positioning of (possibly overlapping)
0124|*pictures with respect to the current text.
