0134|- [HelpText]
0135|*The default plotting unit (minimum step) is 0.1 mm in Survo PostScript
0136|*plotting.
0137|*On high resolution printers (600 dpi or more) this is not accurate enough
0138|*especially in curve plotting when best possible quality is demanded.
0139|*Therefore the plotting unit can be altered by a specification
0140|*PS_UNIT=<step> where PS_UNIT=0.1 is the default setting.
S   |         <    >
0141|*For high quality curve plotting PS_UNIT=0.01 is recommended.
0143|*Too accurate units should be avoided since the largest permitted size is
0144|*SIZE=32767,32767 i.e. about 32.7 cm x 32.7 cm for PS_UNIT=0.01 .
0146|*The following example (next page) illustrates the difference.
0149|[
0150| *PLOT X(T)=R*COS(T),Y(T)=R*SIN(T)
0151| *R=10 XDIV=0,1,0 YDIV=0,1,0  HEADER= FRAME=0
0152| *T=0,2*pi,pi/120 pi=3.14159
0153| *DEVICE=PS,K1.PS
0154| *SIZE=1500,1500       PLOTTING WITH DEFAULT RESOLUTION
0155| *LINETYPE=[BLACK][line_width(0.48)]
0156| *................................................................................
0157| *PLOT X(T)=R*COS(T),Y(T)=R*SIN(T)
0158| *R=10 XDIV=0,1,0 YDIV=0,1,0  HEADER= FRAME=0
0159| *T=0,2*pi,pi/120 pi=3.14159
0160| *DEVICE=PS,K2.PS
0161| *SIZE=15000,15000
0162| *PS_UNIT=0.01         PLOTTING IN 0.01 mm RESOLUTION
0163| *LINETYPE=[RED][line_width(0.48)]
0164| *................................................................................
0165| *PRINT CUR+1,END TO K.PS / Red curve is smoother than the black one.
0166| * [scaling(35,35)][home(-550,-3000)]
0167| * picture K1.PS
0168| * picture K2.PS
0169| *
0170| *
